place_description:
Raw Crunch and Coffee is a fun, family-owned coffee shop nestled in the heart of Indian Trail, NC. Our coffee and milks are all organic, including our house made syrups. We are the only coffee shop in the nation that is proudly free of "natural flavors"! We are also known for our gluten free French crepes and house made Raw Crunch® bars. Coffee in the front, Raw Crunch® bar factory in the back. Whether you're looking for a quick pick-me-up or a relaxing place to unwind, stop by and taste the difference. Lets bring real flavor back!
Thanks a Crunch,
Ross & Kathy

reviews_data.review_text: Raw Crunch is the best coffee shop in the area! I love the organic options they offer while not breaking the bank.
Only stopped here because a family member needed the restroom. Did order a cafe mocha while waiting. Surprisingly one of the best I had. Staff was also very helpful.
Our favorite coffee shop in Indian Trail!
My daughter Jessie and I visited Raw Crunch Coffee . She is a big fan of the shop. I tried her drink and found it to be quite nice ! The food smells delicious !

My absolute favorite coffee shop! They use top-of-the-line ingredients, everything is delicious, love the environment from the decor to the incredible staff. It's just a wonderful place and love to support small businesses. Absolute gem.

It's beautiful, cozy, you feel like family, and it's ORGANIC!!!! Ditch drinking chemicals and make Raw Crunch your new place to get your favorite drink, and the crepes and parfaits are delicious too. Feel good knowing you're supporting a local business while getting clean ingredients and no "natural flavors". Raw Crunch is just the best and the owners are the sweetest!

We visited for the first time yesterday, and we loved it!! We are gluten free and eat clean, and it's such a treat to have a place to go where you can get DELICIOUS treats that fit those bills. We had both crepes, they were perfect...flavor, texture, and the sweet wasn't too sweet. We also had a cappuccino, pumpkin spice latte, and peppermint mocha...all delicious. HIGHLY RECOMMEND!!

Raw Crunch and Coffee is a great place to go if you're looking for organic, great tasting coffee with other organic food options! The decor is quite cozy and makes for a very enjoyable experience. My only complaint is that the hours are very limited.
Crapes are Great! The Raw Crunch Bars are Great! The Coffee has the 'Best Flavor' around! And the Service is Fantastic! It's truly my Favorite Place For Coffee on The Planet!
Best coffee in town
This is a lovely coffee shop. It's my second or third time meeting for a ThinkCrunchy networking event, and I would happily return.
Always happy to stop by here for coffee. Good coffee good service . Love this place !
Salted Carmel lattes  I will come here everyday for those!
Iced Carmel lattes are phenomenal
stopped here and ordered a drink that i ended up not liking when i got it, and they traded it out immediately for a great one. cozy location and kind people; will definitely come here again!
My go to spot, love this place. Great coffee and ownership is awesome.  A++ it's a must.
The inside is decorated so cute  and the staff were very friendly and engaging! I ordered a iced pumpkin spice latte and banana bread. It was sooo good!!
I find myself here 1-3x week to get out of the house and do some work. Good drinks, good food, good people. Highly recommend supporting this local business.

I wish I could review the products but since they are only open 8-12 on a Saturday I was unable to. This is why people go to places like Starbucks because their hours are more accommodating to their patrons.

This place is a little gem!! They really care about their ingredients.
The lattes and the food are clean organic. I recommend the parfait, crepes and banana bread.

Cute lil spot, the atmosphere is nice & the ppl are friendly!!  The Nutella crepe was delicious.
Parking could be tricky if it's at a busier time but we had no problems bc we arrived almost at closing time. Love the idea of the rosemary latte- wish it had a rosemary sprig in it tho. Overall liked this place!!
Crepes over cooked & overpriced. The latte didn't event taste like coffee, too milky. Staff was rude. Won't be coming back.
Great experience and great coffee every time we go to Raw Crunch!
There is nothing else like this in our area. The quality of their coffee and matcha is unmatched. Raw Crunch has absolutely spoiled me and I don't go anywhere else for my matcha and coffee fix now!

I have frequented this shop since it has opened. I've tried seasonal drinks, chai, crepes, kids drinks, they're homemade bars and my all time favorite.. iced matcha. Everything I've had is delicious and made with quality ingredients which I care a lot about. The owners are super sweet and the place is so cute. Will continue to be a loyal customer and recommend all my friends and family.

Great customer service and Coffee! Slightly on the pricey side but worth it since it's organic! Love the inside it was very calm with a farmhouse, industrial, boho aesthetic. Met up with a friend which was amazing! Overall it was great supporting a local small businesses!
Amazing coffee and service, the staff is always friendly! The best coffee shop in the area!
I come in every morning and even twice a day sometimes, great service, very friendly staff and locally owned. Coffee and the crepes are exceptional easily the best coffee shop in the area.
The cutest hidden gem cafe! Delicious coffee and crepes. Don't be deceived by the strip mall location. Super friendly service and lovely interior. Highly highly recommend.
Terrible experience
Coffee was cold and crape overcooked and not sweet, overpriced and service was not very friendly.  Last time I spend my money here, very dissatisfied
Nice place
Our favorite coffee place anywhere in Charlotte. We are from Oregon and none of the local coffee shops in the area compared until we found this place. Love it

Ordered the Rosemary Brown Sugar latte. Sounds unusual but was informed that this was the house take on lavender. Absolutely wonderful, would make the drive from Waxhaw any time for this. Will be back!
I love your coffee! You are the best.
For 40 bucks before tip, I expected more. Coffee was flavorless and the crepes were too expensive for what you get, which isn't much. Cold, small, and without a clean way to eat.

Cute place and cute decor for sure. But the girl at the cash register seemed almost bothered when I was giving her my order. I ordered two Nutella crepes with a cup of milk and I paid $30. The crepes were crispy, not soft, they barely had any Nutella (pictures attached). I asked for the strawberries on the side for both and they only did it for one. And they put the five strawberry slices in a separate cup. Yes,5 slices. Not what I expected with the 4.8 star review.

Love this place! Iced/hot vanilla lattes are delicious! Also love the trailblazer crepe :) this is one of my go-to places because of the quality of their ingredients and the staff is friendly! My husband and I both love it here.

Cute shop but latte didn't taste like coffee at all.
Took couple sips and could only feel milk.
Order took very long to get. Workers were not professional.
Crepe with Nutella was ok but too small for a price.
Yogurt parfait had couple drops of honey and not even a full cut strawberry.
Overall, not going to return.
Our FAVORITE local coffee shop! We regularly stop in at least once a week. The owners are so friendly. The coffee is all organic which is delicious and so hard to find!
Tried once, and done... Not enough options.

I pass by here pretty often and finally went in for some coffee since there are no good coffee shops otherwise. Great coffee, wish they were open more hours but I get it! Super friendly staff, made me feel welcome and had good recommendations.

Great selection!! Fun vibe!! Excellent crepe -we got the savory ham one. We sat outside with our dog Louie and the sweet staff spoiled him with treats. Wonderful way to start the day!! We will be back!

Stopped in to get coffee for friends who are local and just had a baby. The owners were so kind, service was helpful and friendly, and the coffee was AMAZING! Highly recommend this place and the dark chocolate crunch bars.

This is the best coffee shop we have ever found. They are a friendly, customer focused shop that also has yummy baked goods. Forget those large chain coffee shops with products that come from gosh knows where. This place is all organic and top quality!
You really need to try this place out!

Wow! This is like a boutique experience for coffee connoisseurs. All ingredients are clean organic and thoughtfully purchased. One of my favorite things about this place is the passion that the owner has for clean food and how joyful she is in sharing it with others. Coffee is one of the food items that is most heavily processed and traditionally produced coffee can retain toxins. I've had some of their baked goods in the past and they are wonderful also.

Stopping for coffee is a guilty pleasure of mine, but there is no need for guilt here - it's all good clean enjoyment.

The atmosphere is modern and welcoming. It would be a more fun place to meet friends if there were some comfy squishy chairs.

I will be back and bring my friends!

Seriously wonderful coffee, great flavor and great preparation. High quality ingredients, no weird  additives or chemicals which is what brought me in to begin with. Their crepes are super yummy and the service is also great!
One of my favorite local spots for work space and coffee!
My vas liubim, luchshaia kofeinia!

Crape over priced and small, does not taste good. I have not finished mine.

Coffee is just ok, I have not finished mine iced coffee.

Good atmosphere.
Lovely coffee shop, friendly ladies working there and delicious coffee and food. Would recommend to everyone how is looking for a cozy atmosphere.... Also, super clean! :)

We absolutely love having an organic coffee shop around the corner from us! We always stock up on their whole been coffee to have a home. It's incredibly delicious! We tried both varieties and both are super! The family that owns it are the nicest and most welcoming people. I love all the little touches they have especially the coloring pages for the kids. Wish them all the best success!!
Great experience!

Absolutely adore this place. Every morning I come in I'm greeted with a smile. Lovely people and the atmosphere is so welcoming and warm. I would suggest getting the Flat white coffee (if you like something a little bitter) otherwise their parfaits are really good as well!

This place is amazing! A dark chocolate iced mocha is now my new favorite drink. Very kind employees with great recommendations on their menu. I am so glad I found this hidden gym. I had no idea organic coffee is far superior to regular. I hope to be back frequently and possibly make this a new remote work hangout. They serve crepes as well and gave away one of their homemade granola bars for free. Take note that there is not a large seating area so you might want to go there early or at an off hour if you prefer to sit while you drink. There is also minimal parking if the connected businesses are busy. The only negative is I would not recommend having an important meeting or consultation here due to lack of privacy and the ease of hearing other's conversations.
Great coffee, crepes and ambiance!
Great place to meet your friends or make new ones
Amazing gem in our town. Top notch organic ingredients , thank you for choosing only the best to offer.

The only organic coffee place around! Coffee and food is very good! Atmosphere is pleasant and service is wonderful. Highly recommend!
Just wish they were open later, and especially on Saturdays.
Hands down best coffee around! Also the crepes they are making there are insane. Highly recommend.
Great customer service and fresh food and coffee
Coffee was not good unfortunately, the prices are high though, the workers weren't particularly happy or anything like that.

I really wish this place was closer to home but I would drive the 14 miles just to enjoy the best coffee in town!! The menu is very interesting and what I ordered was the Rosemary with brown sugar latte . It was simply the most delicious, exotic and different latte, a kind of drink that warms your heart and soul, a drink that keeps you trying to guess the next ingredient in your drink! I give this place 50/5 stars!! Staff is friendly, service was quick and price is very reasonable . Very clean and cozy (don't judge this place by the outside, is like judging a book by its cover). I call this place my "happy fancy classy" but not pricey coffee place! I highly recommend you pay them a visit
Espresso was delicious! Organic spots are hard to find and much appreciated!

Love what Raw Crunch Coffee is doing in our community! This is the best coffee shop in Indian Trail! Delicious coffee, crepes, & more! I appreciate that the owners are taking an organic approach to coffee & food! They are the only restaurant in Indian Trail that is Diner Friendly/Approved on the Seed Oil Scout App for having organic, clean, whole ingredients! My family loves the ham cheese spinach tomato crepe, & the blueberry lemon crunch parfait. The coffee is good quality, & the london fog has been a perfect tea drink for this cold weather. The price is worth the QUALITY!

Super cute place. The workers were very kind, and the vibes were nice. I ordered the rosemary brown sugar latte, and I gotta be honest: Ive never had rosemary in coffee. Lemme tell ya, it is very yummy. I'm excited to come back and try their crunch bars!

Vegan Pumpkin Spice Latte! Delicious and real 
They also, have a raw vegan PSL bar that was to die for! Go check them out

Love this tiny little gem. The coffee was amazing, the crepes too. The inside vibe is wonderful, and the restroom was clean and cute. I can't wait to go back and try their matcha because before I left someone had ordered it and it looked goooood.

A lovely craft coffee experience in the heart of Indian Trail. Kind and friendly staff await to take and make your order. Coffee is wonderful and their seasonal drink specialties are always excellent, and most of the ingredients are always crafted in-house.
Quick and friendly service. Great vibe in the room. Delicious coffee and food.
First time visitor in this Great little spot for a pick-me-up. Friendly staff, friendly guests and A Fantastic Pumpkin Spice Iced Coffee!
Delicious espresso, matcha lattes, and scones
I'm super picky with my espresso and this place is top notch! The owner is very thoughtful about having safe organic ingredients for her coffee and food items. Highly recommend.

Coffee was pretty good here. My wife got a vanilla latte that she enjoyed, and I just got a straight black coffee. I will say, you need to ask for two cups whenever you get just hot black coffee. It scortches your hand, but doubling it up helps a lot.

Had to meet the boss for "coffee." This place was located just right according to my search for organic coffee. Ordered a 12 oz coffee and asked for dairy-based cream, (because there's no substitute for dairy). "We have half-and-half or heavy cream." Heavy cream? - I'm in. Was expecting a bit of bitterness and disappointment in the coffee, but it was just the best. Got a Raw Crunch bar and promised myself that I'd have to find an excuse to come back.

Top place, good service, pleasant people, all organic and actually very good coffee that had a chocolate-like aftertaste. I'm a fan.
Very friendly "corner" coffee shop in the middle of a little strip of stores.  Great coffee. We'll be back.
Amazing coffee and crepes served by amazing people.
The coffee is good and the staff is attentive and friendly. They could pay a little more attention to the cleanliness of the seating area.

Good coffee but not so great hours. It blows my mind how coffee shops are not open on Sundays when they could receive the most business. Just stopped by and they were closed on Mondays without updating their google hours. Just frustrating.
Amazing
Best gluten-free coffee in town!
Fun, trendy place in a downtown area devoid of interest. Great coffees, hot and cold teas, etc. excellent and efficient service. Limited hours and closed on Sunday.
Great place. Good staff.
Kind staff, amazing coffee, amazing ham and cheese crepe made with high quality ingredients. My new Thursday work spot.

You know... I thought I found my coffee "watering hole" a while ago, but Raw Crunch and Coffee has turned out to be it. They know their customers by name, the entire staff is so kind, and I cannot get enough of their coffee. If you are looking for the professional barista, beautifully cooked beans, and amazing food while you work or visit with a friend - you will want to come to Raw Crunch and Coffee. They are family.
I had drip coffee- it is so cute inside!! Everything is organic, they had different espresso drinks as well as coffee. They also had some bakery items and even had some vegan options.

If you are a local and have yet to try some of the wonderful selections available... my dear you are missing out. Thank you Leah for the referral. I enjoyed a Medium caramel latte. It included organic caramel which they get from Asheville, NC. I also devoured their delicious Trailblazer Crepes, and purchase two of their Raw Crunch Bar: Blueberry Lemon and Mango Coconut (You can actually identify the ingredients).
The only 10/10 coffee shop

This coffee shop is amazing! Discovered them from Instagram and had to check them out immediately. Their coffee is very good and they use organic ingredients and you can definitely taste a difference with their coffee. Their breakfast crepe is very good too. Great customer service as well!

I am thrilled that I found this place. I ordered Ham&Cheese Crepe and Iced Vanila Latte with Oatmilk. The coffee was good! Also, the Crepe was delicious (but a little bit pricy for me).
I will visit again with my kids and will try the Strawberry Nutella Crepe :)

* It opens until 3pm (Mon-Fri,Sat 12pm).

I tried a Jasmine Peach White Tea  today. It was good :)
Good coffee but pricey

We love Raw Crunch and Coffee! Family owned and run, it is some of the best coffee I have ever had. As an added bonus, it is all organic!! A true gem for Matthews and Indian Trail. Highly recommend you check this place out!

Lovely cafe, modern boho decor, original artwork on the wall, beautiful plants, and great staff.

We had the matcha latte, the chai tea latte, the sweet crepe, the savory crepe, all were delicious.
Love love love!!!!! I swear I needed this! They have Pumpkin Spice coffee as a solid menu item! I'm sold.
Really cute coffee shop, convenient location close to Hwy 74. Service was very quick & friendly!  Excited to try some different drinks here in then future.

Great service and friendly people.  Unfortunately, I've tried the drip coffee on a few occasions and it's always super weak.  Please double the grinds and I'll come back to support local once again.  Thank you for considering.

This is my first time visiting this place. I was looking for a good cup of iced coffee and man I found it!! Great service, truly natural ingredients and great tasting coffee... I am sold!! This place is not near my home but I will have to make it a regular in my routine for sure!! PS - HIGHLY recommend the Nutella iced coffee!!!

It was good place :) and very kind.
I will go again!!
11/10 best coffee i've ever had
Most incredible coffee I've ever had
Staff was super nice and helpful. The vanilla iced latte was very good. It had just enough flavoring, but you could still appreciate the taste of the coffee. Will definitely be back.

1st time there and great experience.  It's all that I look for in a coffee shop and MORE!  These guys go all the way with not only organic coffee and ingredients but, also compostable flatware and plates!  And even recycle bins to put them into when you're through.  Small, quaint and a little hidden gem.  This place is my new fave and my new go-to stop on this side of town!
This place is so cute and cozy!   Coffee is great and the craps are light fluffy and tasty.  Definitely recommend!!!

My wife and I each got a a crepe (the "hearty" one and a sweet, nutella-y one with strawberries) and considered coming back for another 2 hours later, hah! On top of that, my americano and her iced mocha with oat milk were the best coffees we had between Indian Trail and Matthews.

I'm a big fan and will definitely be back!

Adorable cafe with the most delicious crepes I've had in a long time! They have a great selection of coffees (I got the chai latte), a variety of baked goods, protein bars & of course the crepe. The service was amazing & the vibe makes you want to come back daily. Loved, loved!

I came here randomly to work and have some coffee and I'm so glad I did! The customer service is amazing. You can tell the owner and staff really care about what they do and who they serve. You can tell in their drinks as well. So yummy! I tried a Chocolate Peanut Butter Latte which I thought was so creative and it was delicious. I will definitely be coming back to work and try more of their drinks and pastries!
Amazing Coffee! Great food!

I recently visited Raw Crunch and Coffee in Indian Trail, North Carolina and I was pleasantly surprised! The coffee was amazing and full of flavor. The baristas were incredibly friendly and knowledgable about the coffee, which made me feel confident about my selection. The atmosphere was cozy, and the shop was impeccably clean and inviting. The snacks and pastries were delicious, with a wide variety of options to choose from. I will definitely be returning soon!
Great customer service. The food was very tasty. Loved the Better the Nutella crepe.
Highly recommend the pumpkin spice latte. They use real pumpkin puree it's so good
Food was delicious people are amazing must try

This place is a hidden gem! They take their coffee very seriously (all organic coffee, no natural flavors used, or gums or oils in their plant-based milks). All these things are very important to me, as well as the availability of gluten free and dairy free pastries and other treats. If you're like me and this is important to you, this is your place! The two employees are so sweet, and I love that you can order online through Odeko! All around a great place for coffee.
Love this new place!

I had a perfectly dialed in double shot here. My cafe au lait had wonderful milk texture. Wonderful atmosphere and very nice staff. I'll be coming back soon not just for the coffee but for the Nutella crepe as well!

My wife told me this place had opened and I was skeptical as a coffee nerd.  I was impressed.  Barista pulling authentic shots on the La Marzocco with their fresh roasted beans (organic too). Great space inside that is done up really nice.  When you think coffee bar (perhaps third wave), you think of a place like this...and now we have one in Indian Trail, which is awesome.

I'm so glad Indian Trail has a new coffee option.  This place is not to be overlooked.  I had their breakfast crepe and their drip coffee.  Coffee was the best I've had in a while, full bodied but no bitter or acidic taste at all.  Like a good wine.  Love a small family owned business.
People working are extremely nice! Got a pumpkin latte and it was so delicious!

Camped out here two mornings while my teenager did the Driver's Ed roadwork across the street.   Owner was welcoming and engaging.  Coffee was very flavorful and a substantial cut above the chain stores.  The vegan chocolate chip banana bread was also stellar.
Run, don't walk, to this amazing coffee shop! Organic, clean ingredients with real flavor... you'll find me here just about every day.
This coffee was amazing! I loved the place! Definitely will come back!

Our first time coming here and we got two Carmel Iced Lattes with Oat Milk and two of the savory crepes. It was truly one of the best meals I have had in a very long time.

It is going to cost you more than an average coffee shop but it is all organic so keep that in mind.

Thank you!
What a gem!! The attention to detail is superb. Staff is wonderful and the coffee is incredible. Atmosphere is so well designed and cozy. New favorite spot!
the coffee is sourced locally and tastes very fresh. prices are on par with other cafes and staff was friendly. definitely recommend checking this out if you're in the area!

Came here for the first time today and I was beyond impressed! The cappuccino was delicious and the ham and cheese crepe was yummy/a huge serving size. I love the fact that everything is organic, they prioritize true natural options, and use recyclable/compostable to-go packaging. As a bonus, the shop is decorated super cute with real plants and has a cozy atmosphere. I will definitely become a regular customer!

Love this place! The decor and drinks remind me of Blue Bottle and Philz. Totally clean and relaxed yet still have the vibe. Love the communal table. Coffee is great! So happy to find this hidden gem! Will be back often.

Love the coffee!
Great bunch of women.
Come and try it out!
You'll love it! I promise

The coffee was excellent! Loved the iced caramel latte. The workers were kind and knowledgeable about their products, and the store was tastefully decorated..highly recommend anyone in the area to stop in.

What a fantastic little coffee shop! I had a latte and the ham and cheese crepe...wow! The coffee was excellent and the crepe was warm, fresh and delicious! Loved the everyday atmosphere with no pretentiousness. Just a easy going family business! One of the owners even said I was her #1 customer of the day! I'll be going back soon!

The Mango and Coconut Bar I had was amazing.  All organic and home made. I also had Carmel Latte.  Well balanced and not too sweet.  This coffee shop is a great add to the community.  Excited to have a local small coffee shop to hang out and get some work done away from the office.  The owners are hands on which makes it even better!  Love this place.  Wish you guys the best!

Fantastic little cafe in downtown Indian Trail. All organic gluten-free crepes, espresso, coffee, vegan and regular pastries and more. Can't seem to get enough... I've been here almost every day since they opened! P.S. I didn't even know the crepes were GF until today. Trust me, they're some of the best around!
Best crepes I've ever had! Coffee is delicious too. All high quality organic ingredients. What a gem!

They've found a FAN right here! This coffee is great (thank you god) and the customer service is top tier! The Raw Crunch bars have everything your body loves and nothing your mouth struggles to pronounce (if you get my meaning). All healthy options and sooo tasty! They also offer breakfast crepes for many of you on the go. This place is a vibe! You have to check it out. Enjoy!

Good coffee, good food, good people. Whether you're stopping quick to grab a bite or wanting to stay for a while and drink some coffee it's worth the visit! Free re-fills on drip coffee is a plus too!
I loved it so much  The food was equisite and the crepes were just too good! Service is GREAT! You must come here and have a meal
Mmm....very yum cafe will go again such sweet owner and delish crepes  pls visit Katherine she has great food and yum snacks
the crepes are so amazing  and it's so rustic and aesthetically pleasing
